parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Buckle Receiver Cover Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle receiver cover can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle receiver cover breaks off
exposing internal components
preventing the male end of the buckle from latching into the receiver
and potentially activating the airbag malfunction indicator light.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Whelen LED Light Failure (Ready for the Road Package)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Whelen LED lights can cause erratic flashing, non-functional turn signals, and reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: Front combination wig-wag LED/parking lamp LED/turn signal LED flashes erratically
turn signal does not function
parking lamp does not function
fuse blows in rear window lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wire Insulation Failure (Ready for the Road Package)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The worn-through wire insulation can cause a short circuit, leading to blown fuses, overheating, and potentially a fire.
symptoms: Fuse blows in rear window lights
wire insulation is melted
bare metal is exposed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: Check brake system light comes on
brakes do not function
smoke flows from under the hood
engine catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, go into limp mode, and become undrivable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The wrench warning lamp and check engine lamp illuminate
the vehicle loses all power
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the vehicle cannot be driven
the vehicle will not go over 1 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front axle can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: A clicking noise is heard in the right front tire area
the axle splines wear out
the vehicle does not lock in park
the axle does not come out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become undrivable, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission is damaged after being serviced
the transmission is burned up
the vehicle is towed back to the dealership on a roll-back wrecker.
